01:07:51.710 --> 01:07:52.870
AUDIENCE: Did the
temperature [INAUDIBLE]?

01:07:52.870 --> 01:07:54.960
DR. ALEX FILIPPENKO:
The microwave background

01:07:54.960 --> 01:08:00.390
is the stretched electromagnetic
radiation from long ago.

01:08:00.390 --> 01:08:03.640
So when the universe
was 380,000 years old,

01:08:03.640 --> 01:08:07.870
its temperature had dropped
to about 3,000 or 4,000--

01:08:07.870 --> 01:08:09.940
about 3,000 degrees Kelvin.

01:08:09.940 --> 01:08:12.850
At that point,
electrons combined

01:08:12.850 --> 01:08:15.440
with protons for
the first time ever,

01:08:15.440 --> 01:08:18.890
a process interestingly
known as recombination.

01:08:18.890 --> 01:08:21.614
Because plasma physicists
can ionize gases and then

01:08:21.614 --> 01:08:24.050
they watch them
recombine in their labs.

01:08:24.050 --> 01:08:26.790
But it's happening
for the first time.

01:08:26.790 --> 01:08:28.520
At that point, the
universe becomes

01:08:28.520 --> 01:08:30.490
transparent to radiation.

01:08:30.490 --> 01:08:32.500
Because you don't have
all these free electrons

01:08:32.500 --> 01:08:35.550
that can easily scatter
electromagnetic radiation, OK?

01:08:35.550 --> 01:08:39.010
At that point, 3,000 degrees,
well that's about the sun.

01:08:39.010 --> 01:08:40.600
It's half the sun's temperature.

01:08:40.600 --> 01:08:46.189
So the light waves back then
were optical and near infrared.

01:08:46.189 --> 01:08:49.600
They have stretched
a factor of 1,000.

01:08:49.600 --> 01:08:54.390
In fact, the stretching factor
since that time is 1,079.

01:08:54.390 --> 01:08:56.020
We now know it quite precisely.

01:08:56.020 --> 01:08:59.760
So the waves have stretched
by a factor of 1,079.

01:08:59.760 --> 01:09:01.670
Their typical
wavelength right now

01:09:01.670 --> 01:09:04.590
is in the microwave
region of the spectrum.

01:09:04.590 --> 01:09:09.979
They preserve their black body
spectral energy distribution.

01:09:09.979 --> 01:09:12.450
It's just that now that
black body corresponds

01:09:12.450 --> 01:09:16.010
to 2.7 degrees, which,
you will realize,

01:09:16.010 --> 01:09:19.560
is 3,000 divided by 1,079.

01:09:19.560 --> 01:09:22.920
So the microwave background
is the microwave background

01:09:22.920 --> 01:09:24.424
because of the stretching.

01:09:24.424 --> 01:09:26.840
It's the wavelength that it
has because of the stretching.

